1. *Videćete* šta se dogodilo kada se budete vratili kući. (You will see what happened when you come back home.)
2. Kada *videćete* svoje dete, zaboravićete na sve probleme. (When you see your child, you will forget about all the problems.)
3. *Videćete* da je moj plan savršen za ovu situaciju. (You will see that my plan is perfect for this situation.)
4. Ja *videću* se sa njom večeras i razgovaraćemo o tome. (I will see her tonight and we will talk about it.)
5. Kada *videćete* moju novu frizuru, oduševićete se. (When you see my new haircut, you will be thrilled.)
6. *Videćete* da su moje prognoze bile tačne. (You will see that my predictions were correct.)
7. Oni *videće* da sam ja u pravu kada se desi ono što sam predvideo. (They will see that I am right when what I predicted happens.)
8. Kada *videćete* ovaj predivan zalazak sunca, osetićete se opušteno. (When you see this beautiful sunset, you will feel relaxed.)
9. *Videćeš* koliko je ovaj posao težak kada ga budeš počeo raditi. (You will see how difficult this job is when you start doing it.)
10. Ja *videh* da su mi ključevi ostali u kancelariji. (I saw that I left my keys in the office.)

Note: The word "videćete" is the second person plural form of the verb "videti" (to see) and can be translated as "you will see". The word "videću" is the first person singular form and can be translated as "I will see", while "videćeš" is the second person singular form and can be translated as "you will see". The word "videh" is the first person singular past tense form and can be translated as "I saw".